# Most Important Concept

# Base Case

Without it:

```cpp
void fun()
{
    fun();
}
```

Runs forever.

Eventually:

```text
Stack Overflow
```

Program crashes.

---

# Mental Model

```text
Base Case = Emergency Brake
```

Without brakes:

```text
Car crashes
```

Without base case:

```text
Program crashes
```

---

# Recursion Structure

Almost every recursive function has:

```text
1. Base Case

2. Smaller Problem
```

---

# Example

Factorial

```text
5!
=
5 × 4!
```

Notice:

```text
5!
```

becomes smaller:

```text
4!
```

---

# Recursive Code

```cpp
int fact(int n)
{
    if(n == 0)
        return 1;

    return n * fact(n - 1);
}
```

---

# Step-by-Step

```text
fact(5)

5 × fact(4)

5 × 4 × fact(3)

5 × 4 × 3 × fact(2)

5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × fact(1)

5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1 × fact(0)

Base Case
```

---

Result:

```text
120
```

